WEBVTT

I00
00:00:03.670 --> 00:00:14.365
The current Agent finds the right facts, but buries the priority after the account summary. Improve will make the billing and P1 decision lead every high-risk result.

I01
00:00:14.085 --> 00:00:23.707
Open Improve agent on the existing Agent, then choose whether to describe the correction directly or include a chat that demonstrates it.

I02
00:00:23.427 --> 00:00:33.853
Choose From chats, ask every high-risk response to lead with the billing and P1 decision, and attach the correction conversation that demonstrates it.

I03
00:00:33.573 --> 00:00:43.156
Review the new lead-with-priority behavior, the existing capabilities that must stay intact, and the Evals OpenPond will rerun.

I04
00:00:42.876 --> 00:00:49.468
Review the planned change and confirm that it preserves citations and every existing action.

I05
00:00:49.188 --> 00:00:58.900
The same locked Evals make the decision clear: the current Agent misses the new lead sentence, while the updated Agent passes every original and new Eval.

I06
00:00:58.620 --> 00:01:07.666
Apply the update only after that comparison. The existing Agent updates in place, with the successful Evals recorded.

I07
00:01:07.386 --> 00:01:16.879
The improved chat now places disputed billing and the open P1 case ahead of adoption decline while preserving source citations.

I08
00:01:16.599 --> 00:01:25.069
The direct triage action repeats the billing-first result, proving the change works outside chat without breaking the existing workflow.

I09
00:01:24.789 --> 00:01:32.940
Commit the final Agent source with a clear Git message so the exact Profile version remains reviewable and shareable.

I10
00:01:32.660 --> 00:01:45.898
Open Sync to review the committed Profile changes. Confirm sync publishes this version so teammates can use the Agent in chat and hosted sandboxes can attach the same source.
